Both required outputs are written:

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 57 hypotheses, 57 analyses, schema-validated, with `dataset_id`, `model_id`, `harness_id`, `max_iterations=25`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis organized by treatment effects, biomarker–treatment interactions, prognostic factors, equity signals, rare alterations / SNP screen, and the multivariable model.

Key clinical findings:
- **Pembrolizumab benefit is biomarker-conditional.** Strong PD-L1×pembro (continuous p=1.6e-7; ≥50% threshold p=5e-11), TMB-high×pembro (p=4e-4), and a negative STK11×pembro (p=0.002) interaction. In PD-L1≥50% & STK11-WT, pembro raises ORR from 15.4% → 21.7%.
- **Prognostic dominance of disease burden:** ECOG, stage IV, brain mets, weight loss, albumin, CRP, sex (female>male) all robustly associated with ORR.
- **Negative findings:** matched targeted therapies (osimertinib/EGFR, sotorasib/KRAS-G12C, olaparib/BRCA2) show no detectable ORR enrichment; 23-SNP panel has no Bonferroni-surviving hits; rare oncogenic alterations are individually null.
- **Insurance disparity persists after adjustment** (private vs Medicaid +0.089 log-odds, p=0.019 in the full model) — refuting my own iter-25 confounding hypothesis.
